Definition.WordDefinition: Eureka \Eu*re"ka\ [Gr. ? I have found, perfect indicative of ? to find.] The exclamation attributed to Archimedes, who is said to have cried out ``Eureka! eureka!'' (I have found it! I have found it!), upon suddenly discovering a method of finding out how much the gold of King Hiero's crown had been alloyed. Hence, an expression of triumph concerning a discovery. [1913 Webster]

Eureka n 1: a copper-nickel alloy with high electrical resistance and a low temperature coefficient; used as resistance wire [syn: {constantan}] 2: a town in northwest California on an arm of the Pacific Ocean
